ue,"answerSupportedByEvidence":true,"retrievalQualityScore":4.2,"agentExperienceScore":4,"sourcePolicyAdherent":null,"freshnessAdherent":null,"callRationale":["Started with a Firecrawl-focused official-domain Tavily search to establish Firecrawl's MCP and Search context shape.","Ran focused official-domain searches for Exa, Parallel, and Tavily to discover MCP docs and benchmark pages without using outside search tools.","Used Tavily extract on 12 known or discovered official URLs from docs, product blogs, and the Tavily evals repository to get source-backed details for synthesis."],"strengths":["Tavily exposed useful agent controls: search_depth, max_results, include/exclude domains, time/date filters, raw content, and a separate extract tool.","The trajectory hit every expected domain: docs.firecrawl.dev, exa.ai, parallel.ai, and docs.tavily.com.","Parallel and Tavily evidence was discovered cleanly through search, including MCP docs, search-depth docs, and benchmark pages.","The batch extract succeeded for all 12 selected official URLs with no MCP-level failures."],"weaknesses":["Direct Tavily search for Exa was under-complete, returning only Exa's homepage and aggregated docs text; known-URL extraction was needed for the Exa MCP and benchmark pages.","The extract result for Tavily's API reference over-focused on country-list text, so the better search_depth evidence came from the search snippet and best-practices page.","The provider's MCP surface has no usage metadata, and the 5-tool schema footprint was 2752 tokens before any search.","Search and extract outputs were useful but verbose: 19530 raw output tokens across five provider calls."],"notableFailures":["One local harness invocation failed before reaching the MCP provider because the first args file was accidentally written relative to the original conversation repo rather than /Users/ethanaggor/firecrawl-results. It was removed with trash and did not appear as a failed MCP tool call.","No provider-side t